-- Ford Fourth-Quarter Adjusted Earnings of 30 Cents a Share Misses Estimates
-- B y   B i l l   K o e n i g
-- 2011-01-28T12:03:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-01-28/ford-fourth-quarter-adjusted-earnings-of-30-cents-a-share-misses-estimates.html
  Ford Motor Co . reported a fourth-
quarter adjusted profit of 30 cents a share.  The average estimate of analysts surveyed by Bloomberg was
for a profit of 48 cents a share.  The automaker also reported fourth-quarter revenue of
$32.5 billion. The average estimate of analysts in the Bloomberg
survey was $28.46 billion.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bill Koenig at 
 wkoenig@bloomberg.net  